[{"c":"<p>When I survey the wondrous cross</p><p>on which the Prince of glory died,</p><p>my richest gain I count but loss,</p><p>and pour contempt on all my pride.</p>"},{"c":"<p>Forbid it, Lord, that I should boast</p><p>save in the death of Christ, my God!</p><p>All the vain things that charm me most,</p><p>I sacrifice them through his blood.</p>"},{"c":"<p>See, from his head, his hands, his feet,</p><p>sorrow and love flow mingled down.</p><p>Did e'er such love and sorrow meet,</p><p>or thorns compose so rich a crown?</p>"},{"c":"<p>His dying Crimson, like a Robe,</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Spreads o'er his Body on the Tree;</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;Then I am dead to all the Globe,</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;And all the Globe is dead to me.</p>"},{"c":"<p>Were the whole realm of nature mine,</p><p>that were a present far too small.</p><p>Love so amazing, so divine,</p><p>demands my soul, my life, my all.</p>"}]